tags.description: Nuraghe complex with central tower and added structure. The nuraghe is not marked on the IGM map. A large subcircular structure of circa 30m diameter. Complete collapse of internal spaces and heavy vegetation covering the centre of the structure
tags.name: Nuraghe sa Perda 'e s'Obiga (Remains)

tags.description: Complex with main tower joined by a wall with a smaller tower and an antewall with another small tower. Granite. Heavy damage from illegal excavation revealing handmade pottery (pieces of storage jars and probably tegami, shallow plates Middle Bronze Age.
tags.name: Nuraghe Ursu

tags.description: The structure consists of two poorly preserved towers. The western tower is mostly collapsed; it is preserved up to 2m in height in its NW part. The eastern tower rests upon natural rock outcrops.
tags.name: Nuraghe Desfollas (Remains)

tags.description:
Nuraghe complex with a keep and four added towers, built in porphyry, granite and some use of basalt for wedges.  Extensive damage to the structure and thick vegetation
covering the remains. It was a complex nuraghe with a bastion.
tags.name: Nuraghe Lurcuri

tags.description: Nuraghe with a central tower and probably four additional towers and a courtyard. The keep and an added tower are visible. Built in granite and porphyry with basalt wedges.
tags.name: Nuraghe Mindeddu

tags.description: this complex nuraghe originally consisted of at least two towers. The southern tower has survived in slightly better condition.  The entrance corridor is 3.20m long.
